data.name: Birnentart
data.quickTastyDescription: A delightful pear tart with a buttery crust and sweet pear filling, perfect for dessert lovers.
detailedCookingInstructions: Roll out the puff pastry on a floured surface and fit it into a greased tart pan, trimming the edges.
In a bowl, mix the sliced pears with brown sugar, melted butter, cinnamon, and vanilla extract until well coated.
Arrange the pear mixture evenly over the pastry.
Brush the edges of the pastry with the beaten egg for a golden finish.
Bake in the preheated oven for 30-35 minutes or until the pastry is golden and the pears are tender.
Let it cool slightly before slicing and serving.
data.modifiersForBase: Made with puff pastry and fresh pears
